  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Centre Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Position: Centre Executive</strong></p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Complete administrative and operational tasks at the centre</li><li>Work towards attaining student sign-up targets and maximise monthly retention</li><li>Liaise with customers and respond promptly to queries</li><li>Resolve any customer grievances in a courteous and professional manner</li><li>Assist with customer payments and maintain accurate files for auditing</li><li>Update HQ promptly about student enrolment, trial lesson and student withdrawal</li><li>Safeguarding of student welfare and safety</li><li>Ensure the centre is well-maintained with a high standard of cleanliness</li><li>Ensure all classrooms are well stocked with required materials and stationery</li><li>Attend additional training as and when required</li><li>Assist with ad hoc projects</li></ul><p><strong>Experience and qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>“O” Level Certificate or higher</li><li>Minimum 1 year of relevant work experience preferably from Education, Retail, Airlines or any other customer centric industries</li><li>Kind and nurturing when interacting with children</li><li>Professional and courteous when communicating with parents/guardians</li><li>Excellent organisation skills</li><li>Proficient with MS Office and Excel</li><li>Willing to work both weekends and three weekdays</li></ul><p><strong>Company benefits:</strong></p><ul><li>Medical and dental benefits</li><li>Incentive programme</li><li>Birthday leave</li></ul>",
